If a trump (Hearts) was not let, Opponents don't have any cards in the non-trump suit, and they have trump they can randomly choose a high or low ranked trump card.

If the first Opponent to play did play a trump card, the second Opponent to play will only play a higher trump card if the Declarer/Dummy just before in play of the trick has played a higher trump card than the first Opponent played. Then, if the second Opponent to play must play a higher trump card than Declarer/Dummy IF the second Opponent has any trump cards, and can't follow suit.

The opponents, as a team, must always attempt to win a trick by playing the highest ranked card possible - notwithstanding the rules set forth in this document.

If a player plays a trump card, they must play the highest trump card if they can. If a player cannot play a trump card, they may play any card. If a player plays a card that is not the highest card of the suit led, they are said to have "undercut" the suit. If a player undercuts the suit led, the player who wins the trick is the player who played the highest card of the suit led. If a player plays a trump card that is not the highest trump card, they are said to have "undercut" the trump suit. If a player undercuts the suit or trump suit, the player who wins the trick is the player who played the highest card of the suit or trump suit.
